# If you can read this, you have found an invisible file.
#
# Files whose names start with a dot are hidden files. Finder and
# File Explorer do not show them by default, but they are there —
# real files doing real work.
#
# This one is called .gitignore. Nearly every project you will ever
# open has one. Its job: tell git which files to NEVER track.

# macOS Finder leaves these behind
.DS_Store

# Windows Explorer leaves these behind
Thumbs.db
